==English==

===Noun===
'''elative'''

#{{grammar}} The “adjective of superiority”. In some languages such as [[Arabic]], the concepts of [[comparative]] and [[superlative]] degree of an adjective are merged into a single form, the '''elative'''. How this form is understood or translated depends upon context and definiteness.
#:''The elative of ''{{ARchar|[[كبير]]}}'' (kabí:r, "big") is ''{{ARchar|[[أكبر]]}}'' (’ákbar, “bigger/biggest”, “greater/greatest”).''

